Durban - A man, believed to have been involved in a card swapping incident in Howick this week, was arrested thanks to special Automatic Number Plate Recognition cameras placed in uMhlanga Rocks.
Marshall Security spokesperson, Kyle van Reenen, said the the car was seen driving along Durban View Road in uMhlanga Rocks yesterday. 

“With the assistance of police, the car was stopped and searched. The driver was positively identified as being involved in a card swapping incident in Howick earlier this week where a sum of R4 00 was stolen,” van Reenen said. 
In July, new cameras were placed along the N3 before Felix Dlamini (Brickfield) Road. Cameras were also placed along Chris Hani (North Coast) Road near the N2 interchange. AdChoicesADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads
Last year, three men were arrested after the vehicle they were driving was picked up by the ANPR cameras. 

The men were linked to at least five armed robberies. 
The number plates of the Quantum taxi was picked up and police and members of Marshall Security were alerted. 
